"36:38:6" : {s: 36, a: 38, w: 6, r: "قدر", t: "تَقْدِيرُ", l: "تَقْدِير", lc: 5, tl: "taqdīru", lb: "নির্ধারণ, পরিমাপ",e: "(is the) Decree", b: "নির্ধারণ", f: 3, rm: "to measure/decree/determine/stint/straiten, to have power, to be able, a measure, means, ability, a term/decree, doom, destiny, measured, decreed."},
"36:38:7" : {s: 36, a: 38, w: 7, r: "عزز", t: "ٱلْعَزِيزِ", l: "عَزِيز", lc: 101, tl: "l-ʿazīzi", lb: "ক্ষমতা এবং কর্তৃত্বের অধিকারী ",e: "(of) the All-Mighty", b: "পরিপূর্ণ ক্ষমতার মালিক", f: 18, rm: "mighty/potent/powerful/strong, noble/honourable/glorious, resisted/withstood, invincible, overcome (e.g. in argument), exalt, prevail, highly esteemed, precious, glory, vanity, excellent, proud and hard manner, stern."},
"36:38:8" : {s: 36, a: 38, w: 8, r: "علم", t: "ٱلْعَلِيمِ", l: "عَلِيم", lc: 163, tl: "l-ʿalīmi", lb: "পরম জ্ঞানী ",e: "the All-Knowing", b: "মহাজ্ঞানীর", f: 4, rm: "to mark/sign/distinguish, creations/beings, world, science/learning/knowledge/information, aware/know. By means of which one knows a thing, hence it signifies world or creation, because by it the Creator is known. alim (pl. ulama) - one who is learned/wise or knows."},
